3.Title: Qatar Airways Flight Review| Business Class | A330-300 Doha to Cochin
3.Author: Ash Rushil
3.Description: FLIGHT DESCRIPTION __________________________________..This video features my Experience travelling on Qatar Airways,World's 5 Star Airline.The Journey was really splendid and enjoyable.Since I am a frequent flyer on the 5 Star Middle East Airline, I got an easy upgrade from Economy to Business Class.Since the upgrade was done online from Economy to Business Class,I had a limit from using the Oryx First/Business Class Lounge facilities at the Airport.However I had a choice to pay a moderate fee inorder to use the Lounge,which I had neglected.Hence the above video does not feature the Lounge Facilities at the airport during my travel.My flight from Doha Hamad International Airport was carried by an Airbus A330-300,which is a medium haul wide body aircraft.Qatar Airways had around 13 of these in their fleet.This is my second time flying on the Airbus A330-300 on Qatar Airways.I have even uploaded my previous flight video from Cochin to Doha(COK-DOH),flight on Qatar airways A330-300, economy seating.Do check out on my channel.I have been a frequent flyer on QATAR AIRWAYS and have been onboard their A320,A321,A330s,A340-600,B787-8,B777-300ER many times.___________________________________..Flight details are provided below.FLIGHT INFO______________..AIRLINE : QATAR AIRWAYSAIRCRAFT : AIRBUS A330-300FLIGHT NO : QR516DATE OF DEPR : 29 DEC 2019DATE OF ARRIVAL : 30 DEC 2019DURATION : 5HRSSEAT NO : 3KCLASS : BUSINESS ROUTE : DOH- COKICAO : OTHH- VOCI(HAMAD INTL-NEDUMBASSERY INTL )________________..Please do check out my other videos on my channel.Music in this video..Qatar Airways old boarding music.Exotic journeys..Credits goes to original owners.

4.Title: United Flight Storytime
4.Author: Krissy's Travels
4.Description: I switched flights after my flight to LA was indefinitely delayed due to a technical issue. The plane’s software was registering low fuel levels although there was plenty of fuel. 13.Review:
Hey Josh, I caught that you have your airspeed indicator marked with what looks like the CMMS. Did you get that from FlightChops? 
I had just gone back and re-watched the  episode where they discussed the Minimum Maneuvering Speed, and I actually calculated it for the rental that I normally fly even though it has a glass panel so I can put that number in my head along with the best glide in case of engine failure. 
Oh and yes P'cola is one beautiful Sunday flight! Thanks for the great content and inspiration  you provide.
